  <bioghist id="aspace_afe2352dd11ddca7fabda95664066872">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>The Baker Institute for Animal Health is one of the oldest research centers dedicated to the study of veterinary infectious diseases, immunology, genetics, and reproduction.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_7bcab40234a03bd4e150dbb4cfccdfdd">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Institute News and Views, 1987-1995, Veterinary Virus Research Institute Annual Reports, 1951-1975 and memos and correspondence.</p><p> Also, magnet, bookmark, brochure, and notecard, 2009.</p><p> Files relating to the history and accomplishments of the Baker Institute and to John M. Olin, including some photographs, 1950-1997.</p>  </scopecontent>
